# Deploy .net maui app

1. Key Generation
   `cd c:\<path-where-you-want-to-store-this-key>keytool -genkey -v -keystore key.keystore -alias MauiAlias -keyalg RSA -keysize 2048 -validity 10000`
   Hit enter and entery password.
   Then fill out the form.

2. Make sure to have this for anroid buil

<PropertyGroup Condition="'$(TargetFramework)'=='net8.0-android'">
  <!-- Build configuration -->
  <Configuration>Release</Configuration>
  <PlatformTarget>AnyCPU</PlatformTarget>

  <!-- Keystore settings -->

<AndroidKeyStore>True</AndroidKeyStore>
<AndroidSigningKeyStore>key.keystore</AndroidSigningKeyStore>
<AndroidSigningKeyAlias>myalias</AndroidSigningKeyAlias>
<AndroidSigningKeyPass>your_key_password</AndroidSigningKeyPass>
<AndroidSigningStorePass>your_keystore_password</AndroidSigningStorePass>

  <!-- Output type -->

<AndroidPackageFormat>aab</AndroidPackageFormat> <!-- Use aab for Play Store -->
</PropertyGroup>

3. dotnet publish -c Release -f:net8.0-android
4. deploy the signed aab file to play console
